This paper deals with the design of trajectories for multiple drones in a radio access network, which involves optimization problems related to network performance and user fairness. This topic is closely related to several sub-fields of computer science, including networked systems (cs.NI), robotics (cs.RO), information theory (cs.IT), control systems (cs.SY), and multimedia (cs.MM). However, given the focus on wireless communication and network optimization, we believe that cs.NI is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.RO and cs.IT. The other two sub-categories are less likely but still plausible, as they involve techniques and methods that could be relevant to the problem at hand.
